  "description": "Sven Arvid Grén Broberg was a Swedish senior librarian and author, born on December 8, 1878, in Örgryte, Gothenburg and Bohus County. He was the son of wholesaler Carl B. and Fanny Grén of Rossö. Broberg obtained several educational occupational credentials in Gothenburg University and achieved a PhD in 1913. He was an assistant at the Gothenburg city library in 1910, second librarian there in 1915, and first librarian there from 1930 to 1943. He was an active member of different organizations, including the Society for Church Singing Friends, the Western Sweden People's Educational Association, the Committee for Planning Public Concerts in Gothenburg, among others. Broberg authored several papers and edited bibliographic work, among others. His hobbies were music, travel, and hiking in the mountains. Broberg was awarded the Royal Order of the North Star, the Second Class of the Order of Vasa, and the Medal of Merit, among other honors."
